<HEADLINE> Heavy Rains Kill Fifteen in Guatemala </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Heavy rains that have
been pelting Guatemala since Tuesday have caused the death of 15
people.
</P>
<P>
The downpour Thursday destroyed several homes in a
subdivisisonn of the Guatemalan capital, killing three children
and an old woman, said rescue workers.
</P>
<P>
The worst tragedy occurred in the northern department of Alta
Verapaz, some 350 kilometers north of Guatemalan City, where a
vehicle that carried several people tried to cross the Jocochiquin
River and was dragged away by current.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday rescue workers recovered the bodies of eight men
and three women and continued to search for other two children and
two adults.
</P>
<P>
The rains have destroyed two bridges and dozens of houses,
leaving thousands of people homeless especially in the southern
coast and the Atlantic littoral.
</P>
<P>
The rains are the effect of a tropical system that moves in the
Caribbean region and will bring rains for another 48 hours,
reported the Meteorological Institute.  
</P>
</TEXT>
