<HEADLINE> Russian Troops Kill 10 Rebels in Chechnya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Russian federal forces
eliminated 10 militants and detained 20 others suspected of
involving in rebel armed groups during new operations in Chechnya
Friday, Russian media reported.
</P>
<P>
Federal forces killed four rebels planting landmines in the
Chechen capital of Grozny and captured another four gunmen, the
Itar-Tass news agency cited the press center of the Russian
Combined Groupings in the North Caucasus as saying.
</P>
<P>
Six suspects were arrested in the Urus-Martan district, among
them a subordinate of rebel field commander Sagarayev, whose band
has been involved in a number of terrorist bombings, said the
press center.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, federal units conducted a number of successful
operations against the rebels in the republic's mountains, killing
three militants near the Sharo-Argun river, who were driving a
herd of horses carrying weapons, said the press center.
</P>
<P>
After Friday's operations, Russian servicemen found three dead
men, identified as armed gangsters, at a graveyard in the Shatoi
district. Now the federal is searching for wounded rebels in the
area, the press center said.
</P>
<P>
The federal forces also destroyed two cashes of ammunition,
tents, rebel shelters, and two cross-country vehicles, it added.
</P>
<P>
The situation in Chechnya has remained tense since Moscow
announced the breakaway republic was liberated several months ago.
The Russian military has repeatedly said that rebel remnants in
small groups had kept trying to interrupt the normalization of the
population's life and striving to draw local residents in various
destructive activities.
</P>
<P>
Recently, the reports of rising fresh clashes between Russian
troops and the Chechen separatists have appeared more frequently
in Russian media, bringing about increasing fear that the
guerrilla war by rebels is getting intensive and may take some
effect. 
</P>
</TEXT>
