<HEADLINE> 3,793 Ugandan Kids Involved in Road Accidents Since 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 15 (Xinhua) -- A total of 3,793 juveniles,
mostly school children, have been involved in road accidents in
Uganda over the last three years, the newly released police
traffic statistics show.
</P>
<P>
Last year alone, 1,543 juveniles, most of them as pedestrians,
were involved in road accidents, and 217 of these children were
killed by speeding motorists, while 62 died as passengers in
vehicles involved in motor accidents.
</P>
<P>
The statistics also indicate that another 838 were seriously
injured and 381 sustained slight injuries.
</P>
<P>
The figures escalated last year compared to the 1,267 children
involved in motor accidents in 1998 and 983 in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The police attributed the large number of children dying on
Ugandan roads to careless drivers and poor school transport.
</P>
