country's energy sector, including privatizing distribution
companies, improving payment of imported products, increasing
independence of authorities in charge of nuclear problems, and
seeking better efficiency in energy uses.
</P>
<P>
"The EU will continue to help Ukraine in financing the
establishment of capacities of (energy) substitution and other
projects in the energy field with the least cost," said the
communique.
</P>
