<HEADLINE> 1,500 Nepali People Killed in Guerrillas War: Home Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 15 (Xinhua) -- About 1,500 people,
including police, civilians and guerrillas members, have been
killed in the police-guerrillas clashes during the last four years,
said Nepali Home Ministry Friday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 273 civilians, 208 police and 979 guerrillas members
have been killed since the outbreak of insurgency of the ultra-
leftist guerrillas in 1996, Home Minister Govind Joshi told the
press after completing his tour to the guerrillas affected
districts in mid-western Nepal.
</P>
<P>
Joshi said the government is ready to hold talks with the
guerrillas and has started basket funding programs in the
guerrillas-affected areas in order to accelerate the development
activities in the areas.
</P>
<P>
Guerrillas-affected areas are the least developed in Nepal
which encourages guerrillas activities. 
</P>
