<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Undersea Optical Fiber Cable in Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- A 38,000-kilometer
opticalfiber cable system linking 33 countries in Asia and Europe
went into operation today.
</P>
<P>
The subaqueous cable line, which heads west from Britain to the
Republic of Korea on the other side, has a high transmission speed
of 20Gb per second.
</P>
<P>
The line had cost 1.5 billion U.S. dollars and took three years
to build. China Telecom invested 39 million U.S. dollars, or 2.6
percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
The cable system has two landing stations in China, namely in
Shanghai and Shantou, in south China's Guangdong province.
</P>
</TEXT>
