Laffnie de Jager, the number five seeds, look to have an easy
opener against Mexico's Enrique Abaroa and Alejandro Hernandez,
but could have a tough time in the second round if they meet the
fancied Russians Yevgeny Kafelnikov and Marat Safin, the newly-
crowned U.S. Open champion. 
