<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Twelve People Killed In Kashmir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Four militants were killed in a gun fight with local security
forces in Shikari Forests in Rajouri District Thursday evening
while two Indian soldiers and a local defense committee member
died in the encounter, PTI quoted official sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
Indian troops shot dead two militants in Poonch District on
Friday in a gun battle which was still going on, PTI said.
</P>
<P>
Due to the insecurity in the area, authorities in Indian-
controlled Kashmir issued orders Thursday for construction of 1000
household bankers and 100 community bunkers in the shelling prone
areas of border districts of Baramulla and Kupwara, an official
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The construction of the household bankers would be done at the
cost of 20,000 rupees (near 435 U.S. dollars) by beneficiaries
themselves who would be paid 17,445 rupees (about 380 dollars) in
three installments, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The community bunkers would cost 35000 rupees (760 dollars), he
said, adding that, in all, 50 million rupees (108,700 dollars)
would be spent on the construction of the bunkers in the first
phase. 
</P>
</TEXT>
