<HEADLINE> Cambodian Premier Appeals to International Community for Aid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The Cambodian Prime
Minister Hun Sen Friday again appealed to the international
community to provide aid for flood victims in the country.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen made the appealing Friday when he inspected the flood
affected villages in Peamro district, Prey Veng province, eastern
Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
He said the state of the flood is very serious this year, much
more serious than that of 1996.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister highly praised the Cambodian people for
their spirit of self-relief and carrying forward the traditions of
"Khmer people help Khmer people".
</P>
<P>
He has ordered all officials at all levels to cancel all
meetings and seminars and focus their attentions on fighting
against the flood and help the affected people to reconstruct
their homes.
</P>
<P>
According to the preliminary estimates of the National Disaster
Commission of Cambodia, up to now 42,700 households are homeless,
83 people died and many rice fields were destroyed in the flood.
</P>
