<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Orient University Town Opens in North China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The "0rient University
Town" opened today in the Langfang Development Zone in north China
's Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
Almost 10,000 students from a dozen universities in Beijing
will receive higher education in the town, according to a local
education official.
</P>
<P>
The town has been designed to establish a comprehensive
education system and provide various specialties of higher
education, long-distance education and information education.
</P>
<P>
The construction of the town started in September last year by
the Beijing-based Foreign Enterprises Service Corporation (FESCO).
</P>
<P>
The town covers an area of 570,000 square meters and includes
diversified colleges and institutes as well as such facilities as
teaching buildings, a library, a gymnasium, dormitories and an
education development center.
</P>
<P>
The town will be a model for China's joint management between
enterprises and universities on higher education, the official
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
