<HEADLINE> Beijing-Shenyang Expressway Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The expressway linking the
Chinese capital Beijing with Shenyang, capital of Liaoning
Province, in northeast China, has formally opened to traffic, with
the inauguration of the Jinzhou-Shenyang section today.
</P>
<P>
Chinese vice-premier Zou Jiahua presided over the inauguration
ceremony here today.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the expressway began in 1996 and has cost
nearly 20 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The 658.3-kilometer expressway is a major part of China's
national highway network, together with the Beijing-Shanghai and
Beijing-Zhuhai expressways.
</P>
<P>
Its opening is expected to reduce the trip from Beijing to
Shenyang, a major industrial center in the northeast, by nearly a
half. 
</P>
