<HEADLINE> Festival to Showcase HK's Performing Arts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong will hold a
thematic festival entitled "Celebration of Hong Kong Performing
Arts: A Tribute to the New Millennium" between mid-October 2000
and early February 2001 to mark the new millennium.
</P>
<P>
The festival, which features 19 programs in different art forms
with more than 80 performances, will showcase the creativity and
multiplicity of Hong Kong performing arts, according to the
Leisure and Cultural Services Department (LCSD), organizer of the
event.
</P>
<P>
Jeff Ying, LCSD's chief manager in charge of performing
companies and festivals said "Hong Kong arts scene has a
remarkable evolution over the past twenty to thirty years, and
many productions deserve re-staging."
</P>
<P>
He added that in addition to paying a tribute to these
outstanding works, the department also encouraged new ideas and
thoughts to let flourish the local performing arts scene by
organizing the Festival.
</P>
<P>
"The new Millennium provides an exceptional chance to review
the past and set eyes on the challenges of the future," Ying said.
</P>
