<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Third Sino-Russian Economic Symposium Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The Third Sino-Russian
Economic Symposium concluded here today.
</P>
<P>
During the eight-day gathering, sponsored by the Chinese
Academy of Social Sciences (CASS), more than 80 economists and
experts from China and Russia discussed economic globalization,
economic reforms, Sino-Russian economic and trade cooperation and
the economic prospects of the two countries in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Li Tieying, a member of the Political Bureau of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and president of
the CASS, said in a speech at the closing ceremony that the
symposium has served to promote the friendship between social
scientists of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He said expressed the hope that social scientists from the two
countries will further academic exchanges and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Dmitry Lvov, secretary of the Department of Economics of the
Russian Academy of Science, said that the discussion is of vital
importance. He added that he expects more academic cooperation
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the closing ceremony, Li met with Russian economists.
</P>
<P>
The previous two events were held in Moscow in 1988 and 1999
respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
