<HEADLINE> Sensex Drops Sharply on Bombay Stock Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The Sensitive Index (Sensex)
declined sharply on the Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) Friday in the
wake of heavy bull unloading coupled with selling pressure from
Foreign Institutional Investors.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-30 share Sensitive Index opened at 4,666.47 and
gradually moved downwards to the day's low of 4,539.35 before
closing at 4,562.38 as against Thursday's close of 4,671.92,
showing a loss of 109.54 points or 2.34 percent.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-100 index also dipped by 77.41 points to 2,297.93 from
the previous close of 2,375.34. 
</P>
