<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Fund Market Moving within Corrections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- China's domestic securities
investment funds market moved within corrections on Friday,
according to Homeway, China's leading on-line financial and
securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
Of 22 discounted funds, only Fund Jintai and Fund Yuyang
advanced, with the rest either remaining unchanged or declining.
They mainly moved around previous close price levels. The trading
volume of Fund Xinghe was clearly expanded, but those of most
other funds were contracted.
</P>
<P>
As for restructured funds, Fund Jinding's placement expansion
was approved, and its expansion prospectus was published. After
its trading was resumed this afternoon, Fund Jinding went
downwards, reflecting that some holders were reluctant to
participate in the placement expansion.
</P>
<P>
Fund Tongzhi that had moved upwards strongly for two days
opened low today, down 4.4 percent at the close, becoming the top
loser today, followed by Fund Handing, Zhujiang, and Jinding,
which were all restructured funds, down from 1.7 percent to 1.6
percent.
</P>
<P>
Another restructured fund Yuze, however, was the top gainer
today. The market showed that restructured funds still moved in
their own way. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
