<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Former Italian President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
met here today with visiting former Italian president Oscar Luigi
Scalfaro.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said both China and Italy are ancient countries with a
long history and have maintained long-term contacts.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the relations between China and Italy have
developed smoothly since the two countries forged diplomatic ties,
adding that it is on the day of November 6th that the two
countries will enjoy the 30th anniversary of diplomatic relations.
</P>
<P>
As long as the two sides continue developing Sino-Italian
friendly relations, they will promote long-term stability in the
new century, he said.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that China and Italy have identical or similar
views on many regional and international issues, and also
maintained consultation and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He added that China and Italy have paid much attention to
building up the just and reasonable international political and
economic new order, opposing power politics and hegemonism.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also mentioned his talks with Italian Prime Minister
Giuliano Amato at the United Nations Millennium Summit, adding
that two leaders agreed that promoting peace and development
should become the theme of the new century.
</P>
<P>
Scalfaro expressed his best wishes that friendly relations
between Italy and China should be further promoted.
</P>
<P>
Mei Zhaorong, president of Chinese People's Institute of
Foreign Affairs (CPIFA), Wang Guangya, vice foreign minister, and
Paolo Bruni, Italian ambassador to China attended the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The Italian guests are visiting China at the invitation of the
CPIFA. 
</P>
