<HEADLINE> Mireya Luis Aims for Olympic Triple Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SYDNEY, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Cuban ace spiker Mireya Luis
vowed on Friday to win the Olympic triple crown at the Sydney
Games before considering any retirement.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua, Luis, 33, said that "I have no
idea of retirement at the moment as we're fully prepared to win
the third consecutive Olympic title."
</P>
<P>
Luis who returned to the competition venues recently after
injuries, is considered the best spiker in the women's volleyball
world as she has competed in some 1,000 international matches in
her 20-year career.
</P>
<P>
Being a survivor of several surgeries, Luis was the key force
behind Cuba's triumphes in both the Barcelona and Atlanta Olympic
Games in 1992 and 1996. 
