<DOCNO> XIE20000915.0163 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Reports 147.6 Bn USD in Foreign Debt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- China's registered foreign
debt stood at 147.63 billion U.S. dollars equivalent by the end of
June, a drop of 4.2 billion dollars or 2.8 percent from at the end
of last year, the State Administration of Foreign Exchange said
today.
</P>
<P>
Administration statistics show that medium- and long-term debt
accounted for 90.4 percent of the total to stand at 133.41 billion
dollars, down by 3.24 billion dollars from at the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
The outstanding amount of short-term foreign debt was 14.22
billion dollars, down by 960 million dollars, and accounted for 9.
6 percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
In the first six months of this year, China signed new foreign
debt contracts of 8.24 billion dollars, used new debt totaling 13.
27 billion dollars, and repaid principals of 16.12 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Compared with that at the end of last year, the outstanding
amount of sovereignty debt remained almost the same to stand at 47.
36 billion dollars; that owed by domestic financial institutions
declined 7.4 percent to 37.88 billion dollars; that owed by
foreign-invested enterprises dipped 1.9 percent to 46.43 billion
dollars; that by domestic enterprises also remained roughly the
same to stand at 14.64 billion dollars; and that by leasing
companies and other institutions dropped 17.9 percent to 1.33
billion dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
