<HEADLINE> Shenzhen A Share Market Slightly Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen Composite Index
closed at 612.99 points on Friday, slightly down 0.12 points or 0.
02 percent from the last close, at the Shenzhen Stock Exchange,
one of the two bourses in China.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the stock exchange's sub-index also dropped from the
previous close, sliding 17.01 points or 0.36 percent to close at 4,
710.8 points on Friday, with a total turnover of 7.28 billion yuan,
which was 11 percent less than Thursday's 8.18 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The Shenzhen Composite Index Friday opened lower at 612.65
points from Thursday's close of 613.11. The market index touched
the low level of 609.28 points in the afternoon and then rebounded
near the market close.
</P>
<P>
According to Homeway, China's leading on-line financial and
securities advisory company, analysts believe that the Shenzhen
market opened lower, because it was the weekend, when investors
were concerned about the news of the second board market and the
listing of state-owned shares. Only the ST shares performed
actively.
</P>
<P>
South Huiton Co., Ltd. was the top gainer with its price up 6.
86 percent to 16.99 yuan per share.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong Yorkpoint Science &AMP; Technology Co,. Ltd., once the
first stock whose price was over 100 yuan per share in China, was
the biggest loser today with its price down 5.18 percent to 56.16
yuan, hit by heavy selling.
</P>
<P>
Homeway analysts predict that the A-share market is likely to
settle at the 610-point level next week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
