<HEADLINE> Shenzhen B Shares Edge Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen B-share market
posted its fifth straight losing streak to close at 119.12 points
on Friday, which was slightly down 0.04 points or 0.03 percent
compared with the last close.
</P>
<P>
Turnover stood at 44.72 million HK dollars, a drop of 49.11
million or 52.34 percent from Thursday's total, according to
Homeway, China's leading on-line financial and securities advisor.
</P>
<P>
Following the recent tumble, the Shenzhen B-share index
continued to go down in afternoon trading owing to lack of
conviction for a sure direction, which led investors to hold their
money from trading.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues beat decliners by 26 to 23, with eight
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Zhonghao rose 4.84 percent to 0.65 HK dollars, while Health
Mineral added 3.75 percent to 2.49 HK dollars.
</P>
<P>
Shandong Airline shed 2.58 percent to 2.27 HK dollars, while
Livzon Pharm retracted 2.25 percent to 2.29 HK dollars.
</P>
<P>
Homeway analysts predict that the general tone will be on the
negative side and the Shenzhen B-share market is likely to
continue to move in a tight range with light volume next week, as
most investors are cautious to put their money into the market.
</P>
