down a simulated Scud ballistic missile at a height of 35
kilometers, in a spectacularly successful test.
</P>
<P>
This was the eighth in a series of Arrow test-firings and
defense technology experts described it as an impressive
achievement. The missile intercepted a relatively small incoming
missile head on, and developers succeeded in boosting its speed to
three kilometers per second.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak and the Director-General of
the Defense Ministry, Amos Yaron, congratulated the development
