<HEADLINE> Little Girl Depicts Deep Sea Dreaming in Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SYDNEY, September 15 (Xinhua) -- A small girl walked to the
very center of Sydney's Olympic Stadium, depicting a seven-minute
Deep Sea Dreaming at the opening ceremony for the Millennium
Olympics.
</P>
<P>
She spreaded out her beach towel, and put zinc cream on her
nose before the stadium lights were extinguished, leaving her
illuminated by a spotlight.
</P>
<P>
The little girl lay down and fell asleep on the beach towel.
She dreamed about the sea.
</P>
<P>
She swam in a tropical sea surrounded by exotic fish of unicorn
fish, hero fish, angel fish, lionfish, jellyfish, barracuda, eel,
spanish dancer, nudi squid, worm on a hook and groundworm.
</P>
<P>
She rose on a jellyfish, where she was met by eight other kids
wearing speedos and goggles.
</P>
<P>
They were exhorted to swim faster and faster.
</P>
<P>
The Deep Sea Dreaming was composed by Elena Kats-Chernin and
performed by the Sydney Symphony Orchestra and the Sydney
Children's Choir, conducted by Simone Young. 
</P>
