<HEADLINE> Typhoon Causes Little Damage to Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Typhoon Saomai has not
caused much damage to Shanghai as expected and the city has called
off the typhoon alert.
</P>
<P>
But the typhoon which lasted more than 10 hours since Thursday
evening has left more than 20 streets under water. Rain has also
flooded hundreds of homes, but residents have managed to clear
most of the water.
</P>
<P>
Fissures appeared on some flood control structures but did not
cause any great damage. Water at the mouth of Suzhou River did not
rise to a level that was predicted but was still 0.5 meter above
the warning level.
</P>
<P>
By noon, the typhoon had left Shanghai and winds and rain have
abated. 
</P>
