<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangdong Reports Fine Economic Performance in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The January-August period
in economic development in Guangzhou saw steady increases in
industrial production, resident consumption and exports.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics from Guangdong Provincial Statistics Bureau
said the province earned 195.93 billion yuan in industrial added
value in the past eight months, up from 15.46 percent from the
same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Exports continued to surge ahead. Guangdong exported 59.35
billion U.S. dollars worth of commodities from January to August,
up 26.4 percent from the comparable figure of 1999.
</P>
<P>
Along with the faster economic growth, local urban residents
also saw increases in their income. In August, per capita
disposable income for urban families in Guangdong was 743.6 yuan,
up 13.3 from August 1999.
</P>
<P>
The income of residents brought about increases in purchase of
valuable securities, as well as spending of food, garments,
medical expenses, transportation and telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
The province's retail sales of consumer commodities from
January to August amounted to 258.13 billion yuan, up 12.2 percent
from the same period last year. In August alone, the retail sales
volume was 32.47 billion yuan in August, up 3.7 percent from July.
</P>
</TEXT>
