<HEADLINE> Entrepreneur Sets up China's First Individual-funded Drug Control Foundation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- An entrepreneur of the Hui
Nationality in northwest China's Qinghai Province has recently
donated 100,000 yuan to set up China's first individual-funded
drug control foundation, the National Narcotics Control Commission
said today.
</P>
<P>
The 36-year-old Laimaidan Maxianyun promised to inject 100,000
yuan into the foundation each year, and called on Chinese people
of various nationalities to "say yes to life, say no to drugs",
and make greater efforts to fight against narcotics.
</P>
<P>
China now faces a grim drug situation, with a registered drug
population of over 680,000 at the end of 1999. Eighty percent were
male addicts, 78 percent between the ages of 17 and 35, and more
than 490,000 took heroin. 
</P>
