<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Middle East Economic Briefs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The following are economic
briefs from the Middle East countries.
</P>
<P>
ABU DHABI -- Two hundred new farms are to be developed in Al Ain
of the United Arab Emirates (UAE), reported the official news
agency on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Al Ain Municipality and Town Planning Department is
coordinating the project and is seeking tenders from road and
transport contractors for dune and sand levelling.
</P>
<P>
The levelling work must be completed in nine months, according
to the report, an estimated 18 million cubic metres of sand must be
levelled.
</P>
<P>
The Abu Dhabi Municipality has set up nurseries which produce 1.5
million saplings, 20 million flowers and 30,000 other plants a
year, while more than 12,000 farms, covering 27,704 hectares, have
been distributed among nationals.
</P>
<P>
The municipality also provides farmers with financial assistance
to purchase equipment, fertilizer and seeds, according to the
report.
</P>
<P>
Elsewhere in Abu Dhabi, thousands of farms have been created
after levelling the giant dunes which dominate the landscape.
</P>
<P>
At least 3,000 farms are being created around Al Ajban, where
Abu Dhabi Municipality has levelled a 30-kilometre desert area,
bringing the number of new farms to more than 15,000, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
ABU DHABI -- Driven by innovative and trend-setting jewellery
designs, United Arab Emirates' gold demand has risen by 103 percent
over the past five years, according to the World Gold Council
(WGC).
</P>
<P>
D.V. Pathy, WGC's manager for the Gulf states, said the growth
in demand has witnessed, in the first seven months in this year, a
rise of 5 percent compared to the same period in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a press conference to announce the first Pan Arab
Gold Jewellery Design Contest called "Al Ibda'ul Hor", Pathy said
the move is part of the Council's effort for the last three years
to rejuvenate Arabic jewellery by fusing modern designs and finish
while keeping the quintessential elements that define Arabic style,
according to a report of the official news agency on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The contest, which is open to all residents of the Arab world,
is being organized in association with L'Azurde Factory for Gold
and Jewels, the largest single jewellery manufacturers in the
world, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Four foreign groups including a Turkish firm and one
Israeli company are negotiating to acquire all or part of Israel's
debt-ridden United Steel Mills, reported Turkish Daily News on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The other three foreign firms are two from Russia and one from
France.
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Yasar Holding, a leading Turkish company in the food
sector, is investing in American beef cattle, which are considered
to be the highest quality beef cattle in the world, reported
Turkish Daily News on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The company will import 5,000 cattle to establish a research and
breeding farm near Izmir, southwest Turkey, with the aim of
enlivening the stock breeding industry in Turkey.
</P>
<P>
The cattle will be fed and maintained by two American farmers.
After the first results are evaluated, 5,000 more cattle will be
imported in two years and the semen of selected cattle will be
distributed to other breeding farms around the country.
</P>
<P>
The entire project is estimated to cost about 10 million U.S.
dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
