<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 20 Bangladeshis Charged with Planting Bomb to Kill PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 15 (Xinhua) -- A case has been filed Thursday
in a magistrate's court in Gopalganj, 230 kilometers southwest of
Dhaka, with sedition charges against 20 persons for planting a
powerful time bomb allegedly to kill Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina
and her cabinet members on July 21, according to sources of the
ruling Awami League Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Case was filed by Criminal Investigation Department (CID)
in the court of Gopalganj district. Mufti Abdul Hannan, a leader
of Harkatul Jihad, a religious fundamentalist group allegedly
backed by Taliban of Afghanistan, has been made the principal
accused in the case. After the killing attempt was foiled, Hannan
has gone into hiding.
</P>
<P>
An attempt to kill Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina by using a
powerful time bomb at Kotalipara, her home town in Gopalganj
district was foiled. The powerful timing devise in a metallic
container weighing 76 kgs was planted in the ground only 50 feet
from the rostrum from where Hasina had addressed a public rally.
</P>
<P>
The explosive planted in the ground was discovered accidentally
when a local boy detected some wires protruding out from the
ground close to the rostrum. The boy informed local people who
conveyed to police and later an army team of explosive experts
retrieved the bomb.
</P>
<P>
Another similar bomb was found two days after the recovery of
the first bomb. The bomb was found near the Kotalipara helipad
Hasina was due to use to address the rally.
</P>
<P>
CID took one month to investigate the case and arrested three
persons for their alleged involvement in the bomb planting
incident. In the case, the CID said the alleged persons attempted
to overthrow the government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
