<HEADLINE> Visit to UN Summit Very Successful: Musharraf </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Chief Executive
Pervez Musharraf has termed his visit to New York to attend the
United Nations Millennium Summit as very successful.
</P>
<P>
"I am extremely happy and satisfied," he remarked in an opening
statement at a press conference at Karachi Airport immediately on
his return in the wee hours of Friday.
</P>
<P>
According to the Associated Press of Pakistan, Musharraf said
that he had delivered his Millennium speech before 150 heads of
states and governments projecting Pakistan's point of view and met
with 15 leaders and exchanged views with them.
</P>
<P>
He remarked that he was very satisfied that it was a very
successful trip and that "we were able to project Pakistan in a
very effective manner in every aspect."
</P>
<P>
The Chief Executive said that he spoke clearly about the
Kashmir issue at the Millennium Summit and also discussed it with
the world leaders he talked to.
</P>
<P>
He said that his purpose is that the people should take
interest in the matter and think about resolution of this thorny
problem. "To that extent we have been successful," he added.
</P>
<P>
There is an awareness at the international level that Kashmir
is the security problem in the region and it is in the interest of
everyone to defuse the situation and settle the core issue,
observed Musharraf.
</P>
<P>
To another question, the chief executive said that Pakistan-U.S.
relations have their own dimensions and are not linked to U.S.-
India ties.
</P>
<P>
He said his view is that Pakistan's ties with the United States
should be seen independently and "we should not hook it on to US-
India relations."
</P>
<P>
Pakistan will maintain ties with the United States independent
of India's relations, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
