<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Zealand Produces Less Crude Oil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, September 15 (Xinhua) -- New Zealand's crude
petroleum production for the year from July 1999 to June 2000 was
1.27 million tons, 13.1 percent less than in the previous year,
according to Statistics New Zealand.
</P>
<P>
The government statistical body Friday said in a press release
that New Zealand's crude petroleum production was at its highest
level in the year from July 1993 to June 1994, when production
reached 1.88 million tons.
</P>
<P>
The level of crude petroleum production in the country
decreased by 11.1 percent in the second quarter of this year. The
amount produced fell from 334,000 tons in the second quarter of
1999 to 297,000 tons in the same quarter of this year.
</P>
<P>
Production of gas reached 242,645 terajoules in the year from
July 1999 to June 2000, a 9.9-percent increase over the previous
year and the highest annual production to date.
</P>
<P>
In the year, the country refined a total of 1.42 million tons
of crude petroleum, with the output for the second quarter of the
year being 368,000 tons, registering a 12.9-percent increase over
the same quarter of last year.
</P>
<P>
The fuel price indexes show that bulk gasoline prices for
commercial users rose 4.8 percent between the first and second
quarters. Compared with the year to June 1999, bulk gasoline
prices had risen 23.9 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000915.0230 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Zealand Sees Decreasing Crimes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, September 15 (Xinhua) -- New Zealand sees
increasing homicides, hard drug offenses and sex crimes but
decreasing recorded crime in general, according to New Zealand
Police Commissioner Rob Robinson.
</P>
<P>
During the year from July 1999 to June 2000, total recorded
crime dropped 5.1 percent, which represented 23,000 fewer offenses,
Robinson said in the latest press release. He attributed the
reduction to cooperative work with community groups and local
authorities.
</P>
<P>
There were 104 homicides in New Zealand with a population of 3.
8 million in the year, 10 more than the previous year and 2,641
grievous assaults, an 8.9-percent increase. Sexual violation was
up 3.5 percent with 744 cases reported.
</P>
<P>
Despite the increase in homicides, the resolution rates
increased to 78 percent from 70 percent in the previous year.
</P>
<P>
In the capital city of Wellington, crime was down 4.7 percent,
but there were 45 hard drug crimes recorded, a 102.3-percent
increase. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
