<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Spain Hopes to Grab 15 Medals in Syndey Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SYDNEY, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Spain will compete to their
best to grab at least 15 medals at the Syndey Olympic Games, said
Spainish Olympic Committee president here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua, Alfredo Goyeneche said "Spain has
fielded in a contigent of similar scale with that in Atlanta, and
hope to achieve 15 to 20 medals in Syndey."
</P>
<P>
Goyeneche revealed that the medal hopefuls for Spain are those
events of marathon, mountain bike, yachting, judo and swimming,
with World Cup double champion Margarita Fullana in particular
from the women's mountain bike.
</P>
<P>
"She has the potentials to help Spain achieve five to six gold
medals," said the official.
</P>
<P>
Fulluna, who finished first in the World Championships in Are,
Sweden, in 1999, got the nickname "Spidergirl" for her climbing
proficiency, and her ability to ascend with remarkable power and
agility.
</P>
<P>
The 28-year-old woman, with a height of 1.70 meters, had a
gruelling season in 1998 that included a crash at the World
Championships. She then teamed with trainer Gert-Jan Theunisse and
began a low-impact regimen that included swimming, in-line skating
and certain elements of gymnastics.
</P>
<P>
In Atlanta, Spain had garnered 17 medals including five golds,
a sharp drop from the 1992 Barcelona Olympics where they finished
with 25 medals with 13 golds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000915.0252 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Seeks No Less than Three Golds in Women's Weightlifting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SYDNEY, September 15 (Xinhua) -- China's women lifters are
trying to win at least three gold medals at the Sydney Olympic
weightlifting tournaments which start on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
China, women's weightlifting powerhouse, is sending four girls
to the Olympics and has confidence to grab at least three out of
four gold medals, headcoach Zhang Wenxi told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
"We may bag all four golds but we don't want to say that way
because anything is possible." Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese women's lifters will vie for gold medals in the 53-
kg category with Yang Xia, 63-kg through Chen Xiaomin, 69-kg with
Lin Weining and over-70-kg class with Ding Weiyuan.
</P>
<P>
Chen Xiaomin could become the easiest gold medalist for China
after Chen Rui-lien of Chinese Taipei, who won world title in the
event from 1996-99, was tested positive in March for Metandiemone,
an anabolic steroid. Chen was banned from the Olympics last week.
</P>
<P>
Chen Xiaomin was former world record holder when she lifted 107.
5 kilograms in the 64-kg category snatch for a new mark in Asian
Championships in 1997. With Chen Rui-Lien suspended, she has no
other strong challengers in the category.
</P>
<P>
For Yang Xia, it would be much difficult to win the gold medal.
The 23-year-old has to overcome the challenge from Li Fengying of
Chinese Taipei. Li won the world champion and set the world mark
of 121.5 kilograms in the clean and jerk last year.
</P>
<P>
Ding Meiyuan, winner of last year's world championships in
Athens with a total of 285 kilograms, will also has to perform
well when she meets Poland's Agata Wrobel.
</P>
<P>
Wrobel twice smashed the world jerk record in the over-75-kg
and set a new mark of 160 kgs at the European championships in
Sofia on April 28. Her total results of 293 kgs also surpassed
Ding's 285 kgs in the world championships last year.
</P>
<P>
"So we have to be cautious and don't say we can win this gold
although Ding lifted many times more than 293 kgs in the practices,
" Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
Zhang rated Yang Xia's performance crucial to realize China's
medal goal. "Because she compete as an opener. You known there is
a saying that 'good begin half way'," Zhang added.
</P>
<P>
Lin Weining, as same as Chen Xiaomin, will miss her arch-rival
Wu Mei-yi of Chinese Taipei and could hand the gold in the 75-kg
to China if she beats Kim-Soon-hee from South Korea.  
</P>
</TEXT>
