<HEADLINE> Malaysia Records Increased Manufacturing Sales </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The sales value of
Malaysia's manufacturing sector soared by 28.3 percent in July
this year over a year ago, according to the Statistics Department
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The sales value amounted to 28.6 billion ringgit (7.52 billion
U.S. dollars) for the month under review against 22.3 billion
ringgit(5.86 billion dollars) recorded in the same month last year,
the department said in its latest statistics.
</P>
