<HEADLINE> Costa Rica's Arenal Volcano Keeps Active </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The Arenal volcano,
considered one of the most dangerous in Costa Rica, has been
active since last month, experts at the Costa Rican Volcanology
and Seismology Observatory said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The volcano, about 190 kilometers northeast of San Jose, keeps
on spewing out gases and lava. But volcanologist Rodolfo Van der
Laat told Xinhua that the activity is "normal."
</P>
<P>
He said lava began to spew out of the volcano after an
avalanche took place on August 23.
</P>
<P>
The Arenal volcano area has become a major tourist site in the
past few years, but volcanology experts said that at least two of
the tourist areas are located in high-risk parts.
</P>
<P>
Since August 23 the five-kilometer radius around the volcano
has become the security limit, said Van der Laat. 
</P>
</TEXT>
