<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT, September 15 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- Saudi Arabia Thursday criticized Israel for
its "intransigent positions" on the Middle East peace process,
saying efforts should be made to safeguard the legitimate rights
of the Palestinians to return to their homeland.
</P>
<P>
The statement was contained in the speech delivered by Nizar
Obaid Madani, Saudi Arabia's assistant minister of foreign affairs,
at the general debate of the 55th General Assembly session. (
Saudi Arabia-Israel-Mideeast Peace)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- Maintaining U.S. hard-line on Iraq, U.S.
Secretary of State Madeleine Albright said on Thursday that U.N.
Resolution 1284 is the road map for Iraq to follow to get out of
the sanctions.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference at the U.N. headquarters in New
York, Albright, who is here attending the 55th session of the
United Nations General Assembly, said that Resolution 1284 was
adopted by the U.N. Security Council through long and hard
negotiations. (UN-Albright-UN Resolution-Iraq)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BRUSSELS -- Belgium's social situation returned to normal at
midnight Thursday after truckers removed all blockades they had
placed since Sunday in a protest against high fuel prices. In
Brussels, main roads leading to downtown had been cleared and the
whole city showed quiet atmosphere. (Belgium-Road Blockades)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian Deputy Premier Ilya Klebanov said Thursday
that retrieving the crew bodies in the nuclear submarine "Kursk"
sinking in the Barents Sea on August 12 will be "a very difficult
and dangerous technical job" and the government may abandon the
salvage plan. (Russia-Submarine Crew-Salvage)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Four Russian soldiers were killed and seven injured
late Wednesday when a convoy of federal forces was ambushed by
armed rebels in the breakaway republic of Chechnya.
</P>
<P>
The convoy came under rebel fire while traveling on a mountain
road near the southern Chechen town of Urus-Martan, the Itar-Tass
news agency quoted a Russian Interior Ministry spokesman as saying.
(Russia-Chechnya) 
</P>
