<HEADLINE> Mexico to Impose Anti-dumping Quotas to S.Korean Refrigerators </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Mexico's Finance Ministry
began Thursday to investigate imports of South Korean
refrigerators in order to impose anti-dumping quotas on them.
</P>
<P>
Mexico imported 132,459 units of refrigerators in 1999, more
than treble the figure for 1998.
</P>
<P>
Imports have affected the prices of Mexican-made refrigerators
and the earnings of Mexico's domestic refrigerator industry, the
ministry said. 
</P>
