<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Investment in Yugoslavia Increases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, September 14 (Xinhua)---- More than 81 million German
marks (some 36 million U.S. dollars) in foreign investment has
flowed into Yugoslavia since January this year, said the Yugoslav
government on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
At a session chaired by Yugoslav Prime Minister Momir Bulatovic,
the cabinet reviewed current economic trends and its work on
national flight control administration.
</P>
<P>
The Tanjug News Agency quoted a statement released by the
Yugoslav government, saying that foreign investors' interests in
Yugoslavia is growing.
</P>
<P>
According to the statement, a total of 186 companies have been
founded this year, among which 114 are joint-ventures and 72 are
sole proprietorship companies.
</P>
<P>
In the 8 first months of this year, international air traffic
in Yugoslavia has increased by 20 percent, with 1,000 aircraft
flying through Yugoslavia's airspace each day, the statement noted.
</P>
<P>
The government has also approved necessary funds for purchasing
new equipment in order to ensure the safety of flight control
administration. 
</P>
</TEXT>
