<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Germany Bans Two Ultra-right Groups </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, September 14 (Xinhua) -- German Interior Minister Otto
Schily announced on Thursday the government's decision to outlaw
two skinhead ultra-right organizations.
</P>
<P>
The ban on the so-called "Blood and Honor" and its youth
affiliate "White Youth" is regarded as part of measures by the
German government to crack down on extremist right organizations,
which either masterminded or perpetrated many cases of hate
violence in the country.
</P>
<P>
Thirty holdouts of the two groups across the country was
searched and their propaganda material as well as bank accounts
were seized, Schily said.
</P>
<P>
The two groups have 200 and 100 members respectively.
</P>
<P>
Schily said that evidence collected from the skinhead groups
would be later used in taking action against another and more
important ultra-right organization -- the German National
Democratic Party. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
