<DOCNO> XIE20000915.0303 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bagach to be Outsiders of Sydney Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SYDNEY, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Aleksandr Bagach of Ukraine
could be excluded from the Sydney Olympic Games due to drugs
offence.
</P>
<P>
The 33-year-old shot putter, bronze medalist at the Atlanta
Olympics four years ago, was cleared by his national federation
after being tested positive this year for anabolic steroids.
</P>
<P>
International Amateur Athletic Federation (IAAF) spokesman
Giorgio Reineri said on Friday the federation's doping committee
had recommended the case be sent to arbitration. He said the
council would consider the recommendation at a meeting next
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The council invariably accepts the decisions of its own
committee and under IAAF rules Bagach would then be suspended
pending the arbitration panel's decision. Arbitration hearings
take several weeks to convene.
</P>
<P>
Bagach was disqualified after testing positive for the male
hormone testosterone at the 1989 European Cup.
</P>
<P>
Eight years later he was again disqualified for a positive test
for the stimulant ephedrine after winning the gold medal at the
Athens world championships. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
