<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Submit Final Line-up for Men's Team Event </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SYDNEY, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Men's team gold contenders
China have submitted their final line-up for the competition
starting tomorrow afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Five-time world champion Li Xiaopeng will be leading a six-man
contingent which includes Xin Aowei, Huang Xu, Yang Wei, Xiao
Junfeng and last-minute substitute Zheng Lihui.
</P>
<P>
Only Yang Wei and Zheng Lihui will be performing on all six
apparatus, while Li Xiaopeng will skip the pommel horse, Xin Aowei
will not compete in the rings, the vault and floor competition
will be without Huang Xu and the high bars and parallel bars
without Xiao Junfeng.
</P>
<P>
China made two major changes after coming to Australia. All-
arounder Lu Yufu had been called on to replace rings world
champion Dong Zhen, but only saw his Olympic dreams shattered
after injuring his neck in the vault training.
</P>
<P>
Changes would not be allowed to be made after the submittal of
the final line-up. 
</P>
</TEXT>
