<HEADLINE> Postdoctoral Research Team Set Up to Support Steel Works </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, September 15 (Xinhua) -- A seven-member postdoctoral
research station was recently set up in a major Chinese steel
producer in central China to further improve the quality of its
steel products, industrial sources here said.
</P>
<P>
The seven postdocs in the Wuhan Iron and Steel Co. Ltd. in this
capital city of central China's Hubei Province are engaged in
economic research and studies of some complex steel-related areas
such as continuous casting, jointing, and residue treatment.
</P>
<P>
The company's 20 billion-yuan technological upgrading in recent
years has transformed the works into an advanced works. The
research station is urgently needed to solve many technological
problems, said Liu Benren, general manager of the company.
</P>
<P>
The company is among China's well-performing steel works. Its
silicon steel products are considered to be the thinnest in the
country.
</P>
<P>
So far, several other steel works and household electric
appliances producers, such as Baoshan and Chongqing steel
companies and Chunlan and Hai'er groups, have established their
own research stations composed of elite professionals.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
