<HEADLINE> Youth Foundation to Cultivate Talent for Westward Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- China Youth Development
Foundation (CYDF) has decided to launch a personnel training
center in Shanghai to cultivate young management professionals.
</P>
<P>
The training program is scheduled to offer advanced courses for
1,000 local officials, all under age 45, from western provinces,
municipalities and autonomous regions, said Wang Rupeng, director
of CYDF's Promotion Department.
</P>
<P>
Together with the China Association for International Exchange
of Personnel, the CYDF initiated the training courses, called
Project Expectation, and aims to bring in overseas professionals,
technologies and funds into the economically-backward areas in
China.
</P>
<P>
"We are training those local officials to be management
professionals with high vision, creativity, comprehensive ability
as well as deep understanding of conditions in localities," Wang
said.
</P>
<P>
The first group of 40 trainees are from Chongqing Municipality,
and Shaanxi, Sichuan, Gansu and Yunnan provinces. 
</P>
</TEXT>
