<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazilian Coach Claims Drugs Testing "A Farce" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SYDNEY, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Michael Lohberg, a German-born
trainer and psychologist who is now coach of the Brazilian
swimming team, said "clean swimmers" would not win any medals in
the Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
"Either the athlete is claean or they fight for a medal," said
Lohberg, who now trains three Brazilian swimmers including
freestyle sensation Fernando Scherer.
</P>
<P>
"The test is a farce. It serves literally as an alibi for the
International Olympic Committee. The fact that nobody has been
caught in the past few months doesn't mean a thing." Lohberg said.
</P>
<P>
Lohberg said: "Nobody trains in another way. The Brazilians
train like the Americans, like the Russians. An athlete has to
choose whether he is clean or he wins a medal." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
