<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Annan Urges One-Day Ceasefire in DRC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 15 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan on Friday urged all the parties concerned in the
Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) to observe one-day ceasefire
throughout the country.
</P>
<P>
The Olympic Games began today in Australia when a worldwide
ceasefire is observed.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued by his spokesman's office, Annan said he
made the appeal so that the third and final polio vaccination
round can be carried out in the country.
</P>
<P>
Annan trusted that a peaceful and secure environment will be
provided to allow the World Health Organization and the United
Nations Children's Fund to give all Congolese children under the
age of five protection from the crippling disease of polio.
</P>
<P>
Fighting in DRC broke out in August 1998 when rebels, backed by
Rwanda and Uganda, accused DRC President Laurent Kabila of
corruption and harboring Hutu militiamen who fled Rwanda after
committing genocide there in 1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
