<HEADLINE> 800 Million People in the World Suffering From Hunger: FAO </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The report says that under-nourishment has fallen especially in
populous Asian countries.
</P>
<P>
Famine now only occurs in exceptional circumstances, the
reports notes, but Africa is still a major focus of concern.
</P>
<P>
The last 15 years have seen a larger number of food emergencies
arising from natural or human-induced factors, and the latter have
been increasing steadily, from about 10 percent in 1984 to over 50
percent today, the report says.
</P>
<P>
For example, economic loss from conflicts in developing
countries exceeded total food aid to them in the '80s and '90s.
</P>
